                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Bergham</surname>, clerk</persName>, acknowledges to have
               received of <persName>sir <forename>Milo</forename> de <surname>Stapulton</surname>
                        </persName>,
               <persName>sir <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>White</surname>
                        </persName>, kts., 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Oliver</forename> 
                           <surname>Groos</surname>
                        </persName>, 
               <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename>, parson of <placeName role="parson" key="place_104500">Salle</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> 
                           <surname>Wurlyk</surname>
                        </persName>, and
               <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Hawys</surname>
                        </persName>, 10 marks sterling, for the term
               ending Michaelmas, of one annual rent of 20 marks, for the life of 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Margery</forename> 
                           <surname>Nerford</surname>
                        </persName> out of the manor of
               <placeName type="manor" key="place_104117">Shotesham</placeName>. 
               Dated in the church of <placeName key="place_104539">St. Christopher, London</placeName>, 8 Oct., <origDate notBefore="1404-09-30" notAfter="1405-09-29">6 Hen. IV</origDate>. 
                
               . </p>
